BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-138@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260222T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260222T210000
SUMMARY:Dueling Duets- Coleman Williams + Lightnin' Luke
LOCATION:Stone Church\, 210 Main St\, Bellows Falls\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Dueling Duets- Coleman Williams + Lightnin' LukeSlow PonySunday February 22Minimum age:All agesShow time:7:00 PMDoors open:6:00 PMStone ChurchTicketsDescriptionJoin us for a special evening of Dueling Duets featuring Coleman Williams IV & Lightnin’ Luke of The Bridge City Sinners!Coleman WilliamsAs the great-grandson of Hank Williams Sr., grandson of Hank Williams Jr., and only son of Hank 3, Coleman spent years waging an internal battle with the expectations thrust upon him by others about his own lineage.Determined to blaze his own trail, Coleman left town after high school and traveled across America. Trying to create a unique sound that would fill his songs with his stories while still trying to show love to his country roots and his Nashville home.Coleman finally channeled his love of the weird into his first album Southern Circus with former band mate Jason Dietz. After the release in 2022, he was able to continue extensive touring and refine his sound with new bandmates. Now leading to the upcoming follow up record Hang Dog. Produced by Shooter Jennings and being released November 17th, 2023. He hopes to show people a journey of love for his old dog and the strange moments in life that can define us. Finding a balance between spectacle and spirit, melodies and muscle. Making the music of a man honoring his family tree while planting his own garden.Lightnin' LukeLightnin' Luke's powerful vocals, heartfelt lyrics, and wild fiddle playing have made him a versatile musical force, and a towering presence in the underground folk music scene. His resume includes a dizzying list of collaborations as a member of The Bridge City Sinners, Yes Ma'am, Tejon Street Corner Thieves, Clyde and the Milltailers and King Strang along with on-stage appearances with The Goddamn Gallows, Pete Bernhard (of The Devil Makes Three), Amigo the Devil, IV and The Strange Band, and many many more. Appearing on a majority of the catalogue from Portland indie label Flail Records, Luke has become a defining pilar of the label's unique sound.Slow Pony At the intersection of traditional and contemporary music, Slow Pony is the accordion-centered, organ-adjacent collective led by Eli Dworkin. Drawing from Balkan, blues, tango, klezmer, cumbia, jazz manouche, punk, and Americana, their music is unpredictable, hypnotic, and unmistakably their own. For over two decades, Eli has defied genre as a multi-instrumentalist, vocalist, songwriter, storyteller, and performer, bringing together an ever-changing cast of accompanists to navigate intricate, fiercely composed-yet-improvised material.Known for dark humor, collective awkwardness, and hypnotic instrumental shredding, Slow Pony captivates audiences from weddings, to festivals, to burlesque shows, to mosh pits. Cutting his teeth on the street, Eli is practiced at stopping the passerby in their tracks, and offering song where it's unexpected. With the combined powers of technical mastery and a relentless drive to create, connect, and revolt, every show is a singular experience, impossible to predict and impossible to forget.LineupColeman WilliamsLightnin' LukeSlow Pony\n\nSource: Stone Church\n\nDetails: https://stonechurchvt.com#/events/159674
URL:https://stonechurchvt.com#/events/159674
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-177@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260222T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260222T160000
SUMMARY:The Equivalent Lands
LOCATION:Next Stage Arts\, 15 Kimball Hill Rd\, Putney\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Putney Historical SocietyThe Equivalent LandsA filmed play on 18th-century land disputes that shaped VermontSunday, Feb 22Minimum age:All agesShow time:2:00 PMDoors open:1:30 PMNext Stage ArtsRSVPDescription$10 suggested donationThe Putney Historical Society presents a video screening of The Equivalent Lands, a play written by Joe Greenhoe in 1976. The production dramatizes 18th-century land disputes in the Connecticut River Valley—conflicts between New York and New Hampshire that involved early settlers in southeastern Vermont and are often seen as a precursor to the Revolutionary War. Based on documented historical events, the play features characters whose descendants still live in the region today. A $10 donation will be requested at the door to support the work of the Putney Historical Society.\n\nSource: Next Stage Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169153
URL:https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169153
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-205@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260222T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260222T210000
SUMMARY:Frank Capra's LOST HORIZON (1937)
LOCATION:Epsilon Spires\, 190 Main St\, Brattleboro\, VT
DESCRIPTION:LOST HORIZON (1937, 133 mins). We offer you a radical change of pace for director Frank Capra (It's A Wonderful Life)– adapted by Robert Riskin from James Hilton’s philosophical best-seller. Ronald Colman finds long-sought-for harmony – and love – in the Himalayan mountains. Experience edge-of-your-seat adventure and romance with an exploration of what it truly means to be at peace with oneself. Visually stunning and brilliant on all levels, from the supporting cast including a luminously spirited Jane Wyatt to the gorgeous set design of Shangri-La. This new 4K restoration, including a newly-recovered scene missing for over 75 years, is the most complete version since its original release.Popcorn Provided! Doors open at 6:30pm, Film Begins at 7pm.The National Film Registry honored the film as “an emotional respite to an American public seeking escape from the Depression and yearning for their own personal utopias.”Lost Horizonreceived seven Oscar…Show More\n\nSource: Epsilon Spires\n\nDetails: https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/frank-capras-lost-horizon-1937
URL:https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/frank-capras-lost-horizon-1937
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-238@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260222T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260222T150000
SUMMARY:4th Annual Snow Golf
LOCATION:Putney\, VT\, Putney
DESCRIPTION:We held our inaugural Snow Golf challenge in 2023 on a beautiful snowy day and had so much fun, we’ve made it an annual event! Snow or no snow, seasoned golfer or novice, we always have a great time for a good cause. Once again we’ll be partnering with the Brattleboro Country Club on the design and layout of our challenges and featuring our popular Scott Farm pop up bar. The unique “kid-driven” food cart from Newton’s Curveball Concessions will return as well. There will plenty of reasons to make an afternoon of it and bring your friends and family!\n\nSource: iPutney\n\nDetails: https://iputney.com/event/4th-annual-snow-golf/?instance_id=5174
URL:https://iputney.com/event/4th-annual-snow-golf/?instance_id=5174
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-239@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260223T090000
