BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-178@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260227T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260227T210000
SUMMARY:Johnny Cash! The Man\, His World\, His Music
LOCATION:Next Stage Arts\, 15 Kimball Hill Rd\, Putney\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Johnny Cash! The Man, His World, His MusicAn intimate cinéma vérité portrait of Johnny Cash, onstage and off.Friday, Feb 27Minimum age:All agesShow time:7:00 PMDoors open:6:15 PMNext Stage ArtsTicketsDescription$10 General AdmissionRobert Elfstrom, 1h 34mProduced in 1968, this film comes from early in the career of local filmmaker Alan Dater, who served as the film’s sound recordist. It follows Johnny Cash on the road and in concert with the Carter Family, the Statler Brothers, and Carl Perkins. The film includes rare footage of Cash recording with Bob Dylan at Columbia Studios, where they work together on several songs.The filmmakers also spent time with Cash and June Carter at their home in Hendersonville, Tennessee, as well as with Cash’s parents and children in California. The film returns with Cash to his childhood hometown in Arkansas and features a moving sequence filmed at the Rosebud Reservation in South Dakota and at the site of the Wounded Knee Massacre.Alan Dater will be present at the screening to introduce the film and take part in a discussion afterward. Prior to the screening, a short video interview with the film’s director, Bob Elfstrom, will be shown, discussing the making of the film.\n\nSource: Next Stage Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169539
URL:https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169539
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-207@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260227T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260227T220000
SUMMARY:SHIRAZ: ROMANCE OF INDIA w/ Music Score by Utsav Lal!
LOCATION:Epsilon Spires\, 190 Main St\, Brattleboro\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Trailblazing pianistUtsav Lalimprovises a new score to this ravishing, romantic tale about the building of the Taj Mahal.Based on the romance between 17th-century Mughal ruler Shah Jahan and his queen, this epic silent film is the captivating story behind the creation of one of the architectural wonders of the world, the Taj Mahal. Shot entirely on location in India, with an all-Indian cast, it features lavish costumes and gorgeous settings. Choosing to perform on an instrument that has traditionally been considered unsuitable for Hindustani classical music, Utsav’s innovative handling of a raga blends his diverse musical influences and has left listeners spellbound. Utsav has performed at leading classical concert venues worldwide, including The Kennedy Centre, Carnegie Hall, Southbank Centre and The Bridgewater Hall, Manchester.Shiraz: A Romance of India(1929, 120 Mins), Doors 7:00pm, Show begins 7:30pm."Imperialism for the masses, the movie culture of the 1920s, purveyed…Show More\n\nSource: Epsilon Spires\n\nDetails: https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/shiraz-romance-of-india-w-music-score-by-utsav-lal
URL:https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/shiraz-romance-of-india-w-music-score-by-utsav-lal
END:VEVENT
