BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-179@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260228T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260228T213000
SUMMARY:Corey Harris with Sunny Lowdown
LOCATION:Next Stage Arts\, 15 Kimball Hill Rd\, Putney\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Corey Harris with Sunny LowdownAn evening of acoustic bluesSaturday, Feb 28Minimum age:All agesShow time:7:30 PMDoors open:6:45 PMNext Stage ArtsTicketsDescription$22 Advance / $26 Door / $10 LivestreamCorey Harris is a guitarist, vocalist, songwriter, and bandleader who has carved out a singular place in contemporary blues. Since beginning his career as a New Orleans street singer, Harris has toured extensively throughout North America, Europe, Brazil, the Caribbean, West Africa, Asia, Australia, and New Zealand.In his early twenties, Harris lived in Cameroon, West Africa for a year—an experience that profoundly shaped his musical voice. Deeply rooted in blues tradition, his work expands the genre by weaving in elements of reggae, soul, rock, and West African music. His 1995 album Between Midnight and Day paid homage to acoustic blues traditions, while more than a dozen subsequent releases chart his evolution from interpreter to visionary songwriter.Harris has performed and recorded with an extraordinary range of artists, including B.B. King, Taj Mahal, Buddy Guy, R.L. Burnside, Dave Matthews Band, Tracy Chapman, Wilco, and Natalie Merchant. In 2003, he was featured as artist and narrator in Martin Scorsese’s film Feel Like Going Home, which traced the blues’ journey from West Africa to the American South.In recognition of his innovative and eclectic work, Harris received a MacArthur Fellowship (“Genius Grant”) in 2007, the same year he was awarded an honorary Doctor of Music degree from Bates College. With one foot firmly in tradition and the other in bold experimentation, Corey Harris remains a truly distinctive voice in modern music.Sunny Lowdown is a master of slide guitar, known for deep grooves, slow-burning blues, and a raw, hypnotic sound steeped in tradition. His career began early—at just sixteen, he played his first professional gig backing John Lee Hooker—and has since included collaborations with blues legends such as Hubert Sumlin, Pinetop Perkins, Otis Rush, George “Wild Child” Butler, R.L. Burnside, and Cedell Davis.Lowdown’s 2018 release Down Loaded earned a Blues Blast Music Award nomination, and in 2019 he won the Vermont Blues Challenge, advancing to the International Blues Challenge in Memphis. Whether playing electric or acoustic guitar, Sunny’s approach is understated and powerful—his strength lies in tone, phrasing, and feel rather than flash.This concert is co-sponsored by the Vermont Blues Society.  The Vermont Blues Society is a 501c3 non-profit dedicated to preserving the heritage of blues music through concerts, workshops and education, enhancing opportunities for Vermont-based blues musicians, and insuring that the future of this uniquely American art form is alive and well in Vermont. Website: https://www.vermontbluessociety.orgFacebook:https://www.facebook.com/VermontBluesSocietyLineupCorey HarrisSunny Lowdown\n\nSource: Next Stage Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169559
URL:https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169559
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-227@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260228T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260228T220000
SUMMARY:Jonee Earthquake Band w/ Coffin Flop & Phrogs
LOCATION:Brewbakers\, 48 Emerald St\, Keene\, NH\, 03431
DESCRIPTION:Buy Tickets on Eventbrite 
 
 Buy Tickets 
 
 
 
 
 
 Jonee Earthquake Band  is an American punk band that originally started in 1979, opening for GG Allin and The Jabbers. The band has been playing since. They are well known in the Northern New England punk scene for only playing all ages shows and encouraging and supporting young, inexperienced punk bands. Phrogs  is an Experimental Rock band that blends latin melodies, gothic punk and old school rock n roll. For live performances, Edd-Phrog is on lead vocals and guitar, (lil) Jake is on bass guitar, Riley (Dick) Dickinson is on the trombone, and Loren is on the Drums. The four friends all hail from Claremont, NH and have been making music together for about a decade. They're known for high energy, goofy, awkward sets, and for always being booked with punk bands (although Eddy denies that we are punk). We’re  Coffin Flop , we make doomy swamp sludge from the bowels of Keene, NH. Our inspirations include Crowbar (both in sound and in body mass), Sleep, the ENTIRE Flenser lineup, and OBVIOUSLY Paul Bufano. PLEASE be PATIENT with us, our keyboard player was, in fact, conceived at a CREED show, but we are overcoming that the best that we can! With a sound resembling WET, WET MUD, you’ll need a shop rag to clean the crud out of your ears after one of our sets! Come for the trudging riffs, stay for the rambling banter about late-stage capitalism. Doors are at 7pm and music will start at 730. This show is all ages and seating is limited and also first come first served. Thanks to support from Savings Bank of Walpole, this show has an Access For All option which lets you name your price (you can't buy multiples of this option at the same time, so to buy more than one ticket, it is necessary to do each additional ticket in a different transaction).\n\nSource: Nova Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.novaarts.org/events/joneeearthquake
URL:https://www.novaarts.org/events/joneeearthquake
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-241@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260228
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260301
SUMMARY:Sandglass Theater’s Winter Sunshine Series presents The Fairy Circus
LOCATION:Putney\, VT\, Putney
DESCRIPTION:The Fairy Circus features over twenty turn-of-the-century-style trick puppets. The puppets dance, play instruments, juggle, contort, transform, and fly through the air with the greatest of ease, all to the best-loved music of favorite composers. This show is sure to delight young children and family audiences alike.
For nearly two decades, the Winter Sunshine Series has been a warm beacon during Vermont’s coldest months—bringing laughter, imagination, and shared experiences to audiences of all ages. Sandglass Theater invites families, friends, and neighbors to gather once again this February and celebrate the joy of puppetry together.\n\nSource: iPutney\n\nDetails: https://iputney.com/event/sandglass-theaters-winter-sunshine-series-presents-the-fairy-circus/?instance_id=5155
URL:https://iputney.com/event/sandglass-theaters-winter-sunshine-series-presents-the-fairy-circus/?instance_id=5155
END:VEVENT
