BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-180@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260306T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260306T213000
SUMMARY:Kalos plus Dan Houghton & Rachel Clemente
LOCATION:Next Stage Arts\, 15 Kimball Hill Rd\, Putney\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Twilight MusicKalos plus Dan Houghton & Rachel ClementeHigh-energy trad folk with pipes, fiddle, guitars, and fearless twistsFriday, Mar 6Minimum age:All agesShow time:7:30 PMDoors open:6:45 PMNext Stage ArtsTicketsDescription$22 Advance / $25 Door / $10 LivestreamKalos is a trio of innovative interpreters and composers of Celtic roots music: Eric McDonald, Ryan McKasson, and Jeremiah McLane. Masters of tradition, they purposefully explore its shadowed edges, delivering music of striking complexity, spontaneity, and joyful exuberance. Their sound sets a high bar for traditional repertoire, driven by a pulsing rhythmic energy and deep artistic integrity.Each member brings a remarkably diverse musical background. Eric studied jazz and bluegrass mandolin at the Berklee College of Music before finding his voice on DADGAD guitar. Ryan holds a degree in viola performance and is among the youngest musicians ever to win the U.S. National Scottish Fiddle Championship. Jeremiah, raised with Scottish roots, has studied Indonesian gamelan, West African drumming, and the works of minimalist composers Steve Reich and Philip Glass; his award-winning compositions have also been featured in film.Kalos is a band made for the stage—live performance is their heart and strength. Their close musical partnership, rooted in long-standing friendships, comes alive through an engaging and playful stage presence. Drawing from Celtic, Breton, American, and other traditions, Kalos forges a bold and contemporary path on accordion, guitar, fiddle, and vocals.While firmly rooted in the rich traditions of Scottish music, harpist Rachel Clemente and piper Dan Houghton bring a gritty, avant-garde edge that places them at the forefront of New England’s Celtic folk scene. Both are avid composers, and their repertoire blends original works with traditional melodies. Clemente was crowned U.S. National Scottish Harp Champion in 2016 and earned a bachelor’s degree in traditional Scottish music from the Royal Conservatoire of Scotland in Glasgow in 2018.Houghton, a Scottish piper, flautist, and DADGAD guitarist, has won numerous competitions, including the Scottish Lowland and Border Pipers’ Society “Open Borderpipes” and “New Composition” events, as well as the St. Chartier “Maître de Cornemuse.” He has toured and taught extensively across Britain, Europe, Ireland, America, Asia, and the Antipodes, performing both as a soloist and with ensembles such as Cantrip, the salsa-fusion band Salsa Celtica, Parcel of Rogues, the Celtic rock band Prydein, and Piper’s Den.LineupKalosDan ClementeRachel Clemente\n\nSource: Next Stage Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169579
URL:https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169579
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-248@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260306T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260306T213000
SUMMARY:Kalos plus If You Must Know
LOCATION:Next Stage Arts\, 15 Kimball Hill Rd\, Putney\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Twilight MusicKalos plus If You Must KnowHigh-energy trad folk with pipes, fiddle, guitars, and fearless twistsFriday, Mar 6Minimum age:All agesShow time:7:30 PMDoors open:6:45 PMNext Stage ArtsTicketsDescription$22 Advance / $25 Door / $10 LivestreamKalos is a trio of innovative interpreters and composers of Celtic roots music: Eric McDonald, Ryan McKasson, and Jeremiah McLane. Masters of tradition, they purposefully explore its shadowed edges, delivering music of striking complexity, spontaneity, and joyful exuberance. Their sound sets a high bar for traditional repertoire, driven by a pulsing rhythmic energy and deep artistic integrity.Each member brings a remarkably diverse musical background. Eric studied jazz and bluegrass mandolin at the Berklee College of Music before finding his voice on DADGAD guitar. Ryan holds a degree in viola performance and is among the youngest musicians ever to win the U.S. National Scottish Fiddle Championship. Jeremiah, raised with Scottish roots, has studied Indonesian gamelan, West African drumming, and the works of minimalist composers Steve Reich and Philip Glass; his award-winning compositions have also been featured in film.Kalos is a band made for the stage—live performance is their heart and strength. Their close musical partnership, rooted in long-standing friendships, comes alive through an engaging and playful stage presence. Drawing from Celtic, Breton, American, and other traditions, Kalos forges a bold and contemporary path on accordion, guitar, fiddle, and vocals.While firmly rooted in the rich traditions of Scottish music, If You Must Know (harpist Rachel Clemente and piper Dan Houghton) bring a gritty, avant-garde edge that places them at the forefront of New England’s Celtic folk scene. Both are avid composers, and their repertoire blends original works with traditional melodies. Clemente was crowned U.S. National Scottish Harp Champion in 2016 and earned a bachelor’s degree in traditional Scottish music from the Royal Conservatoire of Scotland in Glasgow in 2018.Houghton, a Scottish piper, flautist, and DADGAD guitarist, has won numerous competitions, including the Scottish Lowland and Border Pipers’ Society “Open Borderpipes” and “New Composition” events, as well as the St. Chartier “Maître de Cornemuse.” He has toured and taught extensively across Britain, Europe, Ireland, America, Asia, and the Antipodes, performing both as a soloist and with ensembles such as Cantrip, the salsa-fusion band Salsa Celtica, Parcel of Rogues, the Celtic rock band Prydein, and Piper’s Den.LineupKalosIf You Must Know\n\nSource: Next Stage Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169579
URL:https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169579
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-251@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260306T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260306T220000
SUMMARY:The Wooden Nickels w/ Liam Grant & Sam Boston
LOCATION:Brewbakers\, 48 Emerald St\, Keene\, NH\, 03431
DESCRIPTION:Buy Tickets on Eventbrite 
 
 Buy Tickets 
 
 
 
 
 
 The Wooden Nickels  are a collective of acoustic musicians and old friends with a rousing take on traditional bluegrass and Americana, including members of Princess Kikou and Poor Monroe. Liam Grant  is a New England guitarist and improviser cut from the American Primitive cloth. The restless guitar explorations, modal epics, and driving uptempo rags recall the likes of Grant's pedagogue, Takoma Records, and the path that was paved by his forebears John Fahey, Robbie Basho, Peter Walker, Max Ochs and later Glenn Jones, Steffen Basho-Junghans, Jack Rose, and others. Bridging that past, Grant evokes the pith of the landscape where he was raised. Instrumental memoirs and ruminations on the banks of the Merrimack River. Amoskeag. And the place where the waters flow around it. Salmon tails up the river, the exodus to Stratton-Eustis and the last night on Dead River before the great flood. Sam Boston  is from Connecticut. He builds instruments, tools, and sound sculptures. His focus is on resonating objects, long-duration events, and attempts at repetition. His latest concentration has been self-modified electric 2x4 duo-chord hurdy gurdies and handmade fretless lap steel guitars - instruments he has built for musicians like Tashi Dorji, Henry Birdsey, Zach Rowden and others. He frequently works alongside his partner Emma Mistele with whom he recorded his last album “ Table Music ” - pieces for an unstable network of oscillators, microphones, and motors resonating through the table on which they were performed. He has additionally worked with Petr Kotik’s S.E.M Ensemble, Nat Baldwin, Manuel J Perez III, The Suncook Symphony, Marie Carroll and recently performed alongside Loren Connors and Bob Bellerue. His forthcoming album “ Dimensional Blinds ,” a composition for Boston’s hurdy gurdies and bilateral stage blinds in 3 second cycles, for the Annex Blues Society label will be released on February 21st. Doors are at 7pm and music will begin at 730! Seating is first come first served! Thanks to support from Savings Bank of Walpole, this show has an Access For All option which lets you name your price (you can't buy multiples of this option at the same time, so to buy more than one ticket, it is necessary to do each additional ticket in a different transaction).\n\nSource: Nova Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.novaarts.org/events/thewoodennickels
URL:https://www.novaarts.org/events/thewoodennickels
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-144@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T220000
SUMMARY:The Slackers
LOCATION:Stone Church\, 210 Main St\, Bellows Falls\, VT
DESCRIPTION:The SlackersThe AttractorsSaturday March 7Minimum age:All agesShow time:8:00 PMDoors open:7:00 PMStone ChurchTicketsDescriptionThe Slackers have been called “the sound of New York” by the New York Times. They were described by Brooklyn Vegan as a “clean mix of ska, reggae, and soul that gets dirtied up by Vic Ruggiero’s tough New York accent.” Decades into their run, The Washington Post noted that the Slackers “remain at the top of their game.”  Since forming in 1991, the Slackers have released 16 albums, 5 EPs, and countless singles. They have performed thousands of energetic concerts for their global fanbase and remain unstoppably prolific.  In their 2025 releases on Pirates Press Records, the EP “Money is King,” an indictment of the powerful as only the Slackers can do, went straight to the top 25 of the Submodern Reports album list. Their single “My Last Star” was a tribute to Hepcat's Greg Lee, fulfilling the final creative vision of the late singer.  The 11-track compilation “Lost and Found Vol.2” had a surprise boogaloo breakout streaming hit with “Diskambobulated.” Their April 2022 album, “Don’t Let the Sunlight Fool Ya,” was the Slackers’ first charting record and qualified the sextet as a Billboard “new artist” – 30-plus years into their career! The power of the Slackers is nothing new to their fans, which number over 150K on social and thousands more via their direct-to-fan newsletter.  The Slackers regularly perform at clubs and festivals around the world. They’ve sold out multiple curated "slackfests" in London, Chicago, Austin, and Anaheim, as well as "5 days in LA" and their "5 boro tour" of New York CityBrooklyn’s Attractors bring Early Jamaican & American Jazz-influenced music smooshed together & delivered in a bite size packageLineupThe SlackersThe Attactors\n\nSource: Stone Church\n\nDetails: https://stonechurchvt.com#/events/153480
URL:https://stonechurchvt.com#/events/153480
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-208@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T213000
SUMMARY:NAKED LUNCH w/ Live Music by Revenant Sea (Sheri Hupfer & Mark Schwaber)!
LOCATION:Epsilon Spires\, 190 Main St\, Brattleboro\, VT
DESCRIPTION:NAKED LUNCH (1991, 115 mins, Dir. David Cronenberg).MATURE AUDIENCES ONLY, PLEASE.Leave logic at the door and embrace our insect overlords in one of the most hallucinatory films ever made! This singular cinematic oddity sprung from the minds of one of the great poets of the 20th century and one of the great filmmakers – and undoubtedly a huge amount of mind-altering substances! In this adaptation of William S. Burroughs’s hallucinatory, once-thought-unfilmable novelNaked Lunch, Bill Lee (Peter Weller aka:Robocop) is an exterminator with a penchant for ingesting pesticides. While hallucinating, Bill begins to take orders from a giant beetle that commands him to kill his wife and flee into the Interzone. There, he meets his wife’s doppelgänger and his typewriter morphs into a cockroach and begins to produce the book that the film is based upon. And that’s just the start of this surrealist masterpiece’s convoluted and…Show More\n\nSource: Epsilon Spires\n\nDetails: https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/naked-lunch-w-live-music-by-revenant-sea-sheri-hupfer-mark-schwaber
URL:https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/naked-lunch-w-live-music-by-revenant-sea-sheri-hupfer-mark-schwaber
END:VEVENT
