BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-148@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T210000
SUMMARY:Moon Walker | Demi the Daredevil |  Sarah and the Safe Word
LOCATION:Stone Church\, 210 Main St\, Bellows Falls\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Moon Walker | Demi the Daredevil |  Sarah and the Safe Word Moon Walker's Wasteland Country TourFriday March 20Minimum age:All agesShow time:7:00 PMDoors open:6:00 PMStone ChurchTicketsDescription In under 5 years, independent Brooklyn-based indie rocker, Moon Walker, has amassed over 100 million streams, sold out shows across America, and developed a loyal and enthusiastic fanbase. He has performed and toured with such artists as Tool, Primus, Coheed and Cambria, Fishbone and Will Wood. His next album “WASTELAND COUNTRY” is due out in the spring, less than a year after the release of his breakthrough fourth album “Is This The World You Wanted?” Demi the Daredevil writes dark theatrical alt-pop for the underdog: music for the weird kids, the overthinkers, and anyone trying to stay human in a world that loves numbness. In addition to influences spanning rock/emo legends like Queen, Green Day, The Used, and My Chemical Romance, Demi also draws upon the imaginative story-telling whimsy of greats like Tim Burton and Edgar Allan Poe to build a fantasy-tinged universe that’s equal parts catharsis and refuge. Demi has toured across the U.S., shared stages with SkyDxddy, TX2, Capstan, Jhariah, Confetti, Van Full of Nuns, WesGhost, Hotel Mira, and RudyWade. He's grown an impressive community resulting in over 20 Million Spotify streams, and 1,000+ fan art pieces, with features including Emo Nite, BuzzFeed, Relix, and The Punk Rock Museum  Sarah and the Safe Word is a cabaret rock band born in Atlanta. Fronted by vocalist Sarah Rose and co-founded with guitarist Kienan Dietrich, the band has built a storytelling world filled with undead pirates, demon racecar drivers, and vampire rodeo sweethearts. With Beth Ballinger on keys and Maddox Reksten on bass, the group delivers their signature blend of energy and theatrical flair across a sonic tapestry of strings, horns, and cinematic soundscapes. Their early work quickly drew industry attention, with Alternative Press hailing their first label release as “a contender for Debut of the Year” and Warped Tour founder Kevin Lyman personally inviting them to join the legendary tour’s 2017 run. Their flair for spectacle later earned them a cameo in the universe of The CW’s The Vampire Diaries, bringing their dark theatricality to the screen. Over the last ten years, Sarah and the Safe Word have cultivated a fiercely loyal community by doing what they do best: crafting big tales, holding space for queer joy, and turning every show into a celebratory ritual for the strange and spectacular. In 2026 and beyond, the band continues to evolve. Come along, the show is about to begin LineupMoon WalkerDemi the DaredevilSarah and the Safe Word\n\nSource: Stone Church\n\nDetails: https://stonechurchvt.com#/events/164869
URL:https://stonechurchvt.com#/events/164869
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-184@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T213000
SUMMARY:Singer/Songwriter Showcase
LOCATION:Next Stage Arts\, 15 Kimball Hill Rd\, Putney\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Twilight MusicSinger/Songwriter Showcasewith Andrea von Kampen plus Early Risers, Jake Klar, and Lizzy MandellFriday, Mar 20Minimum age:All agesShow time:7:30 PMDoors open:6:45 PMNext Stage ArtsTicketsDescription$22 Advance / $25 At the Door / $10 LivestreamEarly Risers, Jake Klar, and Lizzy Mandell will open the evening with a special in-the-round set, leading into Andrea von Kampen’s debut performance at Next Stage.Hailing from Nebraska’s Great Plains, Andrea von Kampen is a singer-songwriter celebrated for her introspective storytelling and captivating melodies. She has shared the stage with Watchhouse, Punch Brothers, The Wood Brothers, and Anaïs Mitchell’s Bonny Light Horseman; released three studio albums; and performed at the Newport Folk Festival and Rocky Mountain Folks Festival. Her headlining tours across North America and Europe have helped her reach a global audience, amassing more than 55 million Spotify streams. In 2022, Andrea made her acting debut in the independent film A Chance Encounter, starring in the film and writing and recording its soundtrack. This fall, she will release a powerful protest EP—an urgent collection of songs confronting resurgent hateful rhetoric in American politics and calling for justice and solidarity.Early Risers craft rootsy, lyric-driven songs marked by close vocal harmonies and rich, varied instrumentation, including banjo, guitar, mandolin, piano, and shruti box. After pursuing solo careers, Ashley and Putnam joined forces in 2015 and have since toured widely across the U.S. and Canada. Their debut album, Making Life Sweet, reached #1 on the Folk DJ Charts, with four songs landing in the top ten.Blending rhythm and groove with grit and honesty, Jake Klar brings a modern Americana sound that weaves rock and pop influences into folk sincerity. His music transforms simple tunes into emotionally resonant stories that linger long after the last note.Lizzy Mandell has released two albums: Made for Flying, which won Times Argus/Rutland Herald Tammie Awards for Best Singer/Songwriter and Best Album in 2012, and To the Moon (2025), created in partnership with fellow Vermonter and multi-instrumentalist, producer, and vocalist Colin McCaffrey.LineupAndrea von KampenEarly RisersJake KlarLizzy Mandell\n\nSource: Next Stage Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/170375
URL:https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/170375
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-210@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T204000
SUMMARY:PEACHES GOES BANANAS! +Director Q&A!
LOCATION:Epsilon Spires\, 190 Main St\, Brattleboro\, VT
DESCRIPTION:PEACHES GOES BANANAS! (Marie Losier, 2024, France & Belgium, 73 min, in English) FOR MATURE AUDIENCES.For 17 years, director Marie Losier has followed the trailblazing, provocative, and taboo-shattering career of artist and musician Peaches. From her early life, to her ascent towards becoming a queer feminist icon, her story is one that has defied expectations and exemplified fearless exploration and rebellion. PEACHES GOES BANANAS is an intimate portrait of this singular artist. Capturing her thrilling live shows, artistic process, close relationships with her family, and her rise to fame, the film is a “poetic…two-decade long conversation between two artists” (The Upcoming). Synopsis courtesy ofFilmMovementCRITICAL ACCLAIM:"The documentary, which follows the career of Canadian musician Peaches... shows why her brand of feminist punk and electroclash has resonated for 20+ years."Rosie Long Decter,Billboard"Shot over 17 years, it mingles intimate personal moments with visceral concert footage, its…Show More\n\nSource: Epsilon Spires\n\nDetails: https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/peaches-goes-bananas-director-q-a
URL:https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/peaches-goes-bananas-director-q-a
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-229@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T220000
SUMMARY:The Great Groove Theory / Reckoners
LOCATION:Brewbakers\, 48 Emerald St\, Keene\, NH\, 03431
DESCRIPTION:Buy Tickets on Eventbrite 
 
 Buy Tickets 
 
 
 
 
 
 Formed in the famous Rynborn Restaurant and Blues Club,  The Great Groove Theory  has been entertaining audiences around the Monadnock region for the better part of twenty years. With one foot firmly in the blues they effectively blend funk, blues and jam into a high energy danceable sound that never disappoints. Rooted in soul and steeped in rock ‘n’ roll,  Reckoners  is a Boston-based band built from some of the region’s most respected and road-tested musicians. Fronted by singer and guitarist Tim Gearan, the group features guitarist and band leader Johnny Trama (Bettye LaVette, The Silks, Dub Apocalypse), drummer Tom Arey (Peter Wolf, The J. Geils Band, G. Love, Vapors of Morphine) bassist Marc Hickox (Bettye LaVette, Charlie Musselwhite), and keyboardist Darby Wolf (Bettye LaVette, Rubblebucket). Together, they channel the grit and groove of classic soul and rock into something timeless and deeply personal. Their self-produced debut album — now streaming on all major platforms — has drawn more than 43,000 monthly listeners and features the standout single “Looking for a Reason” with guest vocals by Susan Tedeschi. Reckoners have been building momentum across New England with sold-out headline shows and support slots alongside artists including Tedeschi Trucks Band, The Wallflowers, and Bonnie Raitt. Their music and live performances were recently spotlighted in Relix Magazine. Find tour dates, music, and more at reckonersband.com (https://www.reckonersband.com/). Doors are at 7pm and music will start at 730. This show is all ages and seating is limited and also first come first served. Thanks to support from Savings Bank of Walpole, this show has an Access For All option which lets you name your price (you can't buy multiples of this option at the same time, so to buy more than one ticket, it is necessary to do each additional ticket in a different transaction).\n\nSource: Nova Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.novaarts.org/events/greatgroovereckoners
URL:https://www.novaarts.org/events/greatgroovereckoners
END:VEVENT
