BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-255@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T194500
SUMMARY:EAST AND WEST (1924) Yiddish Silent Film w/ Live Music by Alicia Svigals & Donald Sosin!
LOCATION:Epsilon Spires\, 190 Main St\, Brattleboro\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Doors open 6pm, Film begins 6:15,  After the film at 7:45pm, Enjoy a very special Jewish Heritage-Inspired Dinner.East and West(1923, 84 mins),is a delicious comedy that bears the distinction of being the earliest surviving Yiddish language film and the earliest recorded performance of Molly Picon, then just 25, already on the path from Yiddish theater to a long career in film, radio, television, and worldwide stage tours with her husband and frequent co-star, Jacob Kalich. A wonderful role model for the renegade in all of us, best known today for her role as Yente the matchmaker inFiddler on the Roof(1971), Picon shines here as a spirited New York girl who loves boxing, eating, and stirring up trouble— and could not be more different from her religious European relatives. Her New World ways turn the lives of her shtetl relatives upside down, much to the exasperation of…Show More\n\nSource: Epsilon Spires\n\nDetails: https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/east-and-west-1924-yiddish-silent-film-w-live-music-by-alicia-svigals-donald-sosin
URL:https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/east-and-west-1924-yiddish-silent-film-w-live-music-by-alicia-svigals-donald-sosin
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vt-event-256@things-we-love
DTSTAMP:20260216T232417Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T194500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T214500
SUMMARY:EAST AND WEST: Dinner & Film Experience!
LOCATION:Epsilon Spires\, 190 Main St\, Brattleboro\, VT
DESCRIPTION:Doors open 6pm, Film begins 6:15,  After the film at 7:45pm, Enjoy a very special Jewish Heritage-Inspired Dinner created byStella Mori Silbert:improviser, audio editor, curator, cook, field recordist, disorganizer of sounds, organizer of multi-disciplinary gatherings in Western Massachussetts.MENU:-Chicken soup (flavor vibe is lemon, parsnip, peas, dill, celery.No noodles, so this hearty soup is accessible to gluten-free folks)- Paprika sauerkraut stew with potatoes and beans (vegan & gluten-free)- Horseradish sour cream (as an optional garnish for the soups)- Rosemary rye challahShow More\n\nSource: Epsilon Spires\n\nDetails: https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/east-and-west-dinner-film-experience
URL:https://www.epsilonspires.org/event-info/east-and-west-dinner-film-experience
END:VEVENT
