SUMMARY:NXT Rockumentary Film Series
LOCATION:Next Stage Arts\, 15 Kimball Hill Rd\, Putney\, VT
DESCRIPTION:NXT Rockumentary Film SeriesA raw documentary about ambition, rivalry, and indie rock excess.Wednesday, May 13Minimum age:All agesShow time:7:00 PMDoors open:6:30 PMNext Stage ArtsRSVPDescription$8 suggested donationJoin us for the next installment of the NXT Rockumentary Film Series. Filmed over several years, this documentary chronicles the volatile rise of two closely linked indie-rock bands whose ambitions pull them in sharply different directions. What begins as camaraderie slowly curdles into rivalry, revealing how ego, obsession, and substance abuse can fracture both creative partnerships and personal lives. Darkly funny and deeply uncomfortable at times, the film becomes a cautionary portrait of how talent alone is never enough to hold a scene—or a friendship—together.Due to licensing restrictions, we’re unable to publicly list the film title. To find out what’s screening, join our mailing list or contact us directly.\n\nSource: Next Stage Arts\n\nDetails: https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169686
URL:https://www.nextstagearts.org/events-calendar#/events/169686
END:VEVENT
